        <briefdescription>
<para>Defining Byte 0x91: PRECR. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Bit[15:8]: Vendor Reserved</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bit[7:2]: Reserved</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bit[1]: Handoff Delay NACK</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bit[0]: Deep Sleep Detected</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>For drivers and help functions, the raw data coming back from target device is in big endian. This needs to be translated back to CPU endianness before passing back to function caller. </para>
